<article class="article-page" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article">
<div class="print-logo">
<img src="//img01.bt.co.uk/s/assets/040319/home/images/bt.png" alt="BT" />
</div>
<meta itemscope itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" itemType="https://schema.org/WebPage" itemid="http://home.bt.com/tech-gadgets/phones-tablets/what-is-tethering-how-to-turn-your-phone-into-a-mobile-hotspot-11364097202959"/>
<meta itemprop="articleSection" content="phones &amp; tablets"/>
<div class="header-section">
<div class="subheader">
<h1 itemprop="headline">
What is tethering? Discover how to turn your phone into a mobile hotspot
</h1>
</div>
<div class="teaser-text-section">
<p itemprop="description">
Did you know you can tether with BT Mobile and share your internet connection with other devices?
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="details-section clearfix">
<div class="details-left" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
<meta itemprop="name" content="BT.com"/>
<a href="//home.bt.com/author/hannah-bouckley-31363802324361" rel="author">
<img src="/images/hannah-bouckley-136380232436106901-180423121707.png" class="thumbs-img" alt=Hannah Bouckley title="Hannah Bouckley" width="26" height="31">
</a>
<div class="details-left-text">
<div>
<span>By</span>
<span class="author-name">
<a href="//home.bt.com/author/hannah-bouckley-31363802324361" rel="author">Hannah Bouckley</a>
</span>&nbsp;
</div>
<div>
<span>Last updated:&nbsp;23 October 2018 - 1.33pm</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="details-right col-lg-4">
</div>
</div>
<div class="hero-image-section" itemprop="image" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject">
<picture>
<source srcset='/images/what-is-tethering-discover-how-to-turn-your-phone-into-a-mobile-hotspot-136409720302902601-160919121613.jpg' media="(min-width: 1200px)" class="img-responsive">
<source srcset='/images/what-is-tethering-discover-how-to-turn-your-phone-into-a-mobile-hotspot-136409720302903901-160919121613.jpg' media="(min-width: 500px)" class="img-responsive">
<source srcset='/images/what-is-tethering-discover-how-to-turn-your-phone-into-a-mobile-hotspot-136409720302910401-160919121613.jpg' media="(max-width: 499px)" class="img-responsive">
<img class="img-responsive" src=/images/what-is-tethering-discover-how-to-turn-your-phone-into-a-mobile-hotspot-136409720302902601-160919121613.jpg srcset="/images/what-is-tethering-discover-how-to-turn-your-phone-into-a-mobile-hotspot-136409720302902601-160919121613.jpg 1024w, /images/what-is-tethering-discover-how-to-turn-your-phone-into-a-mobile-hotspot-136409720302903901-160919121613.jpg 500w, /images/what-is-tethering-discover-how-to-turn-your-phone-into-a-mobile-hotspot-136409720302910401-160919121613.jpg 320w">
</picture>
<meta itemprop="url" content="http://home.bt.com">
<meta itemprop="height" content="365">
<meta itemprop="width" content="648">

</div>
<div class="article-body-section" itemprop="articleBody">
<p>
BT Mobile has a great feature you might not know about that makes your phone even more useful &ndash; tethering.</p>
<p>
Tethering is when you turn your phone into a personal hotspot, so you can get online using other devices.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">
<a href="http://home.bt.com/tech-gadgets/phones-tablets/what-is-wi-fi-calling-new-bt-mobile-service-will-boost-your-smartphone-signal-11364261945076" target="_self"><strong>[Read more: How to boost your mobile phone signal]</strong></a></p>
<p>
For instance you could use it to connect a laptop or tablet to the internet when you are away from home or don&rsquo;t have a wi-fi connection, or you could share your connection with family and friends, allowing them to go online.</p>
<h3>
How to set up tethering on your phone</h3>
<p>
Tethering is easy to enable, the set-up process varies slightly depending on which operating system your phone runs.</p>
<p>
<strong>Android:</strong> Go to the Settings menu. Look for <strong>Network &amp; Internet &ndash; Hotspot &amp; tethering </strong>and switch on <strong>&lsquo;Portable Wi-Fi hotspot.&rsquo;</strong></p>
<p>
You can customise your settings by tapping&nbsp;<strong>&lsquo;Set up Wi-Fi hotspot.&rsquo; </strong>The name of the your hotspot will be filled in, but you can change this and choose a password. Click <strong>'Save' </strong>when you are happy. Give the name and password to people you want to share your connection with.</p>
<p>
Some manufacturers such as LG and Samsung have their own Android phone interface, so settings may vary. Look for &lsquo;Tethering&rsquo; or &lsquo;Mobile hotspot&rsquo; in the menu.</p>
<p>
<strong>iPhone: </strong>For an iPhone look for the <strong>&lsquo;Personal Hotspot&rsquo;</strong> option in the <strong>Settings</strong> menu. <a href="http://bt.com/tethering?s_intcid=con_intban_dmedia_content_btmobile_tethering" target="_blank"><strong>Find out how to set up tethering on an iPhone.</strong></a></p>
<p>
<strong>Windows Phone:</strong> Head to the<strong> Settings</strong> menu and tap <strong>&lsquo;Internet Sharing&rsquo;</strong>. Turn the slider next to Sharing <strong>&lsquo;On&rsquo; </strong>and under <strong>Share over</strong> select <strong>Wi-fi</strong>. Give your phone a name and set up a password.</p>
<p>
To get online using your phone&rsquo;s internet connection, activate wi-fi on the device, look for your phone and enter your password.</p>
<h3>
How to turn off tethering</h3>
<p>
Tethering uses data, so make sure you turn it off when you&rsquo;ve finished to avoid using up your allowance or getting an unexpected bill.</p>
<p>
<strong>Android:</strong>&nbsp;Go to the Settings menu. Look for&nbsp;<strong>Network &amp; Internet &ndash; Hotspot &amp; tethering&nbsp;</strong>and switch on&nbsp;<strong>&lsquo;Portable Wi-Fi hotspot.&rsquo;</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>Apple:</strong>&nbsp;Look for the <strong>Personal Hotspot </strong>option. <a href="http://bt.com/tethering?s_intcid=con_intban_dmedia_content_btmobile_tethering" target="_blank"><strong>Find out about tethering on an iPhone</strong></a></p>
<p>
<strong>Windows Phone:</strong> In the<strong> Settings</strong> menu go to <strong>System &ndash; Internet Sharing</strong> and flick the sider to<strong> &lsquo;Off.&rsquo;</strong></p>
<h3>
Tethering: Things to be aware of</h3>
<p>
Tethering uses your phone&rsquo;s mobile data connection. If you have a relatively small data allowance &ndash; for instance 500MB - and use it to tether, you will run out of data more quickly than normal.</p>
<p>
Go over your data allowance, and you will be charged and could get a larger bill than normal. Avoid this by setting up a monthly spend cap. This means if you go over your allowance, you&rsquo;ll know exactly what the maximum bill will be, and won&rsquo;t be hit with any unexpected bills. Whether or not you set a spend cap you&rsquo;ll get a text when you are close to hitting the cap and when you hit it.</p>
<p>
BT Mobile sets a spend cap of &pound;40, which you can increase or decrease.&nbsp;<strong><a href="http://www.bt.com/mymobile?s_intcid=con_intban_dmedia_content_btmobile_tethering" target="_blank">Set your spend caps by logging into: BT.com/mymobiles</a></strong></p>
<p>
If your mobile data allowance is larger, such as BT Mobile&rsquo;s 20GB tariff, exceeding it will be less of a concern, but it&rsquo;s still worth using the BT Mobile app to check your allowance.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<a href="https://www.productsandservices.bt.com/mobile/?s_intcid=con_intban_dmedia_content_btmobile_tethering" target="_blank"><b>Check out our handset and SIM-only deals</b></a></p>
<p>
