<div class="content-module">
<article class="article-page" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article">
<div class="print-logo">
<img src="//img01.bt.co.uk/s/assets/040319/home/images/bt.png" alt="BT" />
</div>
<meta itemscope itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" itemType="https://schema.org/WebPage" itemid="http://home.bt.com/tech-gadgets/phones-tablets/samsung-galaxy-s10-hands-on-11364332328106"/>
<meta itemprop="articleSection" content="phones &amp; tablets"/>
<div class="header-section">
<div class="subheader">
<h1 itemprop="headline">
Samsung Galaxy S10 and Samsung Galaxy S10+: Hands-on video
</h1>
</div>
<div class="teaser-text-section">
<p itemprop="description">
From their stunning Infinity-O Displays to handy Wireless Power Charging to boost the battery in other phones, take a closer look at the latest additions to Samsungâs smartphone range.
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="details-section clearfix">
<div class="details-left" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
<meta itemprop="name" content="BT.com"/>
<a href="//home.bt.com/author/hannah-bouckley-31363802324361" rel="author">
<img src="/images/hannah-bouckley-136380232436106901-180423121707.png" class="thumbs-img" alt=Hannah Bouckley title="Hannah Bouckley" width="26" height="31">
</a>
<div class="details-left-text">
<div>
<span>By</span>
<span class="author-name">
<a href="//home.bt.com/author/hannah-bouckley-31363802324361" rel="author">Hannah Bouckley</a>
</span>&nbsp;
</div>
<div>
<span>Last updated:&nbsp;28 March 2019 - 2.48pm</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="details-right col-lg-4">
</div>
</div>
<div class="hero-image-section" itemprop="image" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject">
<picture>
<source srcset='/images/samsung-galaxy-s10-front-and-back-136433780898902601-190220144724.jpg' media="(min-width: 1200px)" class="img-responsive">
<source srcset='/images/samsung-galaxy-s10-front-and-back-136433780898940701-190220144724.jpg' media="(min-width: 500px)" class="img-responsive">
<source srcset='/images/samsung-galaxy-s10-front-and-back-136433780898910401-190220144724.jpg' media="(max-width: 499px)" class="img-responsive">
<img class="img-responsive" src=/images/samsung-galaxy-s10-front-and-back-136433780898902601-190220144724.jpg srcset="/images/samsung-galaxy-s10-front-and-back-136433780898902601-190220144724.jpg 1024w, /images/samsung-galaxy-s10-front-and-back-136433780898940701-190220144724.jpg 500w, /images/samsung-galaxy-s10-front-and-back-136433780898910401-190220144724.jpg 320w">
</picture>
<meta itemprop="url" content="http://home.bt.com">
<meta itemprop="height" content="365">
<meta itemprop="width" content="648">

</div>
<div class="article-body-section" itemprop="articleBody">
<p>
Samsung has just unveiled three new stunning smartphones, the Samsung Galaxy S10, Samsung Galaxy S10+ and Samsung Galaxy S10E, all of which are available to&nbsp;<strong><a href="http://www.bt.com/mobile-a/phones/?s_intcid=con_intban_dmedia_content_samsungs10" target="_blank">now from BT Mobile</a></strong></p>
<div class="embed-container">
<iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Jf4mRRvWkRo"></iframe></div>
<h3>
Samsung Galaxy S10 features</h3>
<p>
No space is wasted on the front of the Galaxy S10, which includes an edge-to-edge 6.1-inch Infinitely-O Display. Because there&rsquo;s no home button, you can have an uninterrupted viewing experience when watching your favourite TV programs or movies.</p>
<p>
With Wireless Power Sharing if your friend&rsquo;s phone runs out of power, as long as it&rsquo;s compatible, you can wirelessly share power from your S10.*&nbsp; Take photos with the True Vision Camera which includes a front camera, three rear cameras with an ultra-wide and ultra-zoom lens.</p>
<p>
Keep the contents of your phone secure with the Ultrasonic Fingerprint Scanner, which new to the S10 range. It&rsquo;s actually built into the screen, so you won&rsquo;t accidentally touch the rear camera and smudge it, it also works in low temperatures and sunlight.</p>
<h3>
Samsung Galaxy S10+ features</h3>
<p>
Made from strong aluminium and gorilla glass, the Galaxy S10+ has a 6.4-inch Infinity-O Display, with no home button or notch, which means you get an uninterrupted viewing experience whether watching movies or looking at photos.</p>
<p>
The True Vision camera has not one, but three rear cameras: a 12-megapixel wide-angle, a 12-megapixel zoom for close-ups and 16-megapixel ultra-wide angle for landscapes.&nbsp; There are also two front cameras to help you capture brilliant selfies.</p>
<p>
Like the Galaxy S10, the S10+ includes an Ultrasonic Fingerprint Scanner, Wireless Power Sharing and is dust and waterproof resistant.**</p>
<h3>
Samsung Galaxy S10e features</h3>
<p>
Samsung has also introduced a third Galaxy smartphone. The Samsung Galaxy S10e includes a 5.8-inch Infinity-O Display, Wireless Power Sharing, True Vision Camera and Side Fingerprint scanner.</p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.bt.com/mobile-a/phones/?s_intcid=con_intban_dmedia_content_tech_storefront_samsung_s10" target="_blank"><strong>The new Samsung Galaxy S10, S10+ and S10E are available from BT Mobile.</strong></a></p>
<p>
<span style="font-size:11px;"><em>*Wireless charge compatible (QI standard) devices only. Battery charge above 30% required to PowerShare on the move without being plugged into mains charge. **IP68 water resistant up to 1.5 metres for up to 30 minutes. Rinse in fresh water afterwards.</em></span></p>
</div>
<meta itemprop="datePublished" content='2019-03-28T14:48:26+GMT'/>
<meta itemprop="dateModified" content='2019-03-28T14:48:26+GMT'/>
<div itemprop="publisher" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization">
<div itemprop="logo" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject">
<meta itemprop="url" content="http://img01.bt.co.uk/s/assets/121115/images/BT_logo.png">
<meta itemprop="width" content="102">
<meta itemprop="height" content="50">
</div>
<meta itemprop="name" content="BT">
