    	<h2>Important information</h2>

    


</div>
<div class="text parbase section">

    
    
    	<p><span class="notes"><span class="bold">The legal stuff</span></span></p>
<p><span class="notes">Each year from March 2020, the price of your SIM Only, Data SIM, Family SIM, tablet, mobile phone, mobile broadband, broadband and landline plan and most of our other prices will increase by the rate of inflation (the Consumer Price Index rate published in January of that year). This includes call charges, features and plans. Other terms, prices and products, like BT TV or BT Sport, might also change during your contract.Â See <a href="https://www.bt.com/help/home/#/">bt.com/prices</a> for details.</span></p>
<p><span class="notes">*Family SIM saving compared to the same number of individual SIMs bought on our standard SIM Only plan.</span></p>
<p><span class="notes">See ourÂ <a href="https://www.bt.com/assets/pdf/BT_PhoneTariff_Residential.pdf" target="_blank">tariff guide</a>Â for details of all our standard prices.</span></p>
<p><span class="notes">For full BT Plus terms see <a href="https://www.bt.com/broadband/plus/terms/">bt.com/btplusterms</a></span></p>
<p><span class="notes"><b>BT Broadband</b></span></p>
<p><span class="notes">The BT Reward Card is issued by Blackhawk Network (UK) Ltd., pursuant to license by Mastercard International Incorporated.</span></p>
<p><span class="notes">93% of calls dealt with in UK and Ireland, some specialist teams are located offshore.</span></p>
<p><span class="notes"><b>Complete Wi-Fi guarantee: </b>Weâll send you up-to two more discs to ensure a strong signal in every room of your home. If you still canât get a strong signal weâll give you a one-off credit of Â£20 off your next BT bill.Â Guarantee only applies when your Smart Hub2 is connected to the internet and does not cover broadband faults. For full terms seeÂ <a href="/terms/">bt.com/legalstuff</a>.</span></p>

    


