                        <h4 class="panel-title">
                            <a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse7Standard1-col-parsys--2099087540601269245" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse7Standard1-col-parsys--2099087540601269245"> <span class="icon-down-chevron"></span> <span class="heading-text">
                                What are download speeds and upload speeds?
                                </span>
                            </a>
                        </h4>
                    </div>
                    <div id="collapse7Standard1-col-parsys--2099087540601269245" class="panel-collapse collapse " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="heading7Standard1-col-parsys--2099087540601269245">
                        <div class="panel-body">
                            <div>
                                <div class="text parbase section">

    
    
    	<p>Your download speed is the speed at which you can download or stream things from the internet.</p>
<p>Your upload speed is the speed that you can upload things to the internet (for example, posting photos to social media).</p>
<p>Itâs important to know that the speed ranges we show are an estimate. Theyâre based on homes with similar lines to yours, but there are other things than can affect the speed youâll get â like how many people are using your broadband connection at the time, and whether youâre using a wireless or cable connection.</p>

    


</div>


                            </div>
                            
                                  
                                    
                                
                            
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
              
