<p><span class="notes"><b>Paying for your Pre-Ordered Device</b></span></p>
<p><span class="notes">You might have to pay an upfront fee for your device. If you do, weâll take your bank card details when you apply to pre-order. But we wonât charge your bank card until weâve allocated a device to you. If this payment fails (for example due to lack of funds), your pre-order may be cancelled. You can cancel your pre-order at any point until we charge your card for this upfront fee.</span></p>
<p><span class="notes"><b>Getting your Pre-Ordered Device</b></span></p>
<p><span class="notes">If your pre-order is confirmed, weâll aim to send your new device to you within 30 days of the official launch date, unless we tell you otherwise. Sometimes, we wonât be able to get your device to you within 30 days of the official launch date (because of high demand, for example). If this is the case, and you donât want to wait longer than 30 days, you can cancel your pre-order. But as set out above, you canât do this if we have already charged the upfront fee to your bank card. This does not affect your statutory rights to change your mind within 14 days of receiving your device and only pay for the services you have used. Weâll start charging you for your BT Mobile service in the normal way from the day after weâve dispatched your new device to you and your minimum term will start from that date too</span></p>
